The organic phase from the extraction is separated for crystallization of product B. The saturation concentration of B in this organic solvent at the crystallization temperature of $T_{cryst} = 280$ K is $[B]_{sat} = 0.10$ mol/L. The mass crystallization rate is known to follow the second-order rate law:
$$ \frac{dm_c}{dt} = k \cdot V \cdot ([B]_{sol} - [B]_{sat})^2 $$
where $m_c$ is the mass of crystals (g), $V$ is the solution volume (L), $[B]_{sol}$ is the time-dependent molar concentration of B in the solution (mol/L), and $k$ is the rate constant.

